Stadtwerke-led Group Raises 1 Billion Euros of Wind-Farm Loans

-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 
2011-07-08T08:00:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/stadtwerke-led-group-raises-1-billion-euros-of-wind-farm-loans.html
A group of investors led by
Stadtwerke Muenchen AG raised 1 billion euros ($1.5 billion) of
loans to fund a wind farm in the  North Sea .  The  project financing  for Global Tech I Offshore Wind GmbH
includes 460 million euros of commercial bank term loans, 400
million euros of European Investment Bank-funded term loans
guaranteed by commercial banks, and a 100 million-euro EIB
tranche, arrangers of the financing said in a statement.  Munich-based utility Stadtwerke, HEAG Sudhessische Energie
AG, EGL Holding Luxembourg AG, Esportes Offshore Beteiligungs
GmbH, Windreich AG, FC Windenery GmbH, GTU I GmbH and Norderland
Projekt GmbH are investors in the project that will have 80 wind
energy converters with total capacity of 400 megawatts, enough
to supply 445,000 households, according to the statement.  Dexia Credit Local SA, KfW IPEX-Bank GmbH, Norddeutsche
Landesbank Girozentrale, and Societe Generale SA are initial
arrangers of the deal, the largest project-financed offshore
wind farm, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
